gomodel:SYNGO_4876  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 4d,e,f: Immunoelectron microscopic detection of immunogold labeling of Gγ7 (GNG7) by antisera showed localization to synaptic vesicles in cerebellar parallel fiber, climbing fiber and hippocampal Schaffer collateral presynaptic terminals.\n\nFigure 5c: similar observations are made in GABAergic presynaptic terminals in rat cerebellum. Synapses between basket cell axonal terminals and Purkinje somata were analyzed.. Experimental description: M&M: \"Deeply anesthesized rats were sacrificed by decapitation. The cerebellar cortex was immediately removed and cut into small cubes of about 8 mm3\"\n\nantibody:\n\"The following rabbit polyclonal antisera against G-protein subtypes were used: ... Gγ7 (AS 361; Leopoldt et al., 1997) ... All G-protein subtype-specific antisera were characterized for immunocytochemistry with respect to specificity and crossreactivity (Brunk et al., 1999; this paper).\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2022-09-11" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4876" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

